---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title={"Organize Browser Tabs with Named Tab Groups | Blanc"}
  description={"Group Blanc tabs by name, keep the active group on the Island, and switch between a quiet focused view and the rest of your session."}
  path="/features/tab-groups"
  page="feature-tab-groups"
  current="features"
  ogDescription={"Group tabs by name, keep the active group on the Island, and switch between a quiet focused view and the rest of your session."}
  ogImage="/feature-tab-groups.png"
  ogImageAlt={"Blanc's Island showing a named research tab group over a web page."}
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline slot="head">
{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"BreadcrumbList","itemListElement":[{"@type":"ListItem","position":1,"name":"Home","item":"https://blancbrowser.com/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":2,"name":"Features","item":"https://blancbrowser.com/features"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":3,"name":"Tab groups","item":"https://blancbrowser.com/features/tab-groups"}]}
</script>

<main class="feature-page feature-detail-page">
  <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb"><a href="/">home</a><span aria-hidden="true">/</span><a href="/features">features</a><span aria-hidden="true">/</span><span aria-current="page">tab groups</span></nav>
  <section class="feature-hero feature-hero--detail feature-hero--text" aria-labelledby="groups-title"><p class="section-kicker">a little order</p><h1 id="groups-title">Keep the tabs you need. Tuck away the rest.</h1><p>Name a group for the task in front of you. Blanc keeps that group on the Island and leaves the rest close, not constantly visible.</p></section>
  <figure class="product-capture feature-capture">
    <div class="demo-stage island-figure island-figure--panel" role="img" aria-label="Blanc's Island panel open, with tabs organized into named groups: pinned tabs, a 'social' group, and a 'watch' group holding YouTube and Netflix.">
      <div class="demo-page" aria-hidden="true"><div class="bar w1"></div><div class="bar w2"></div><div class="bar w3"></div><div class="bar w4"></div></div>
      <picture>
        <source media="(max-width: 560px)" srcset="/shots/mobile/netflix.jpg">
        <img class="demo-shot show" src="/shots/desktop/netflix.jpg" loading="lazy" alt="" aria-hidden="true">
      </picture>
      <div class="demo-island open" aria-hidden="true">
        <div class="panel">
          <div class="panel-row"><div class="field"><span class="typed"></span><span class="caret"></span></div></div>
          <div class="list">
            <div class="sec-head"><svg class="ico" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.3" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M5 3h6l-1 5 2 2v1H4v-1l2-2z"/><path d="M8 11v3"/></svg><span>pinned</span><span class="rule"></span></div>
            <div class="trow"><span class="fav" style="background-image:url('https://icons.duckduckgo.com/ip3/gmail.com.ico')"></span><span class="title">Gmail</span><span class="dom">mail.google.com</span></div>
            <div class="trow"><span class="fav" style="background-image:url('https://icons.duckduckgo.com/ip3/notion.so.ico')"></span><span class="title">Notion</span><span class="dom">notion.so</span></div>
            <div class="sec-head"><svg class="caret" viewBox="0 0 10 10" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.4" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M3.5 2 L7 5 L3.5 8"/></svg><span>social</span><span class="rule"></span><span class="count">1</span></div>
            <div class="trow"><span class="fav" style="background-image:url('https://icons.duckduckgo.com/ip3/threads.net.ico')"></span><span class="title">Threads</span><span class="dom">threads.net</span></div>
            <div class="sec-head"><svg class="caret" viewBox="0 0 10 10" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.4" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M3.5 2 L7 5 L3.5 8"/></svg><span>watch</span><span class="rule"></span><span class="count">2</span></div>
            <div class="trow hl"><span class="fav" style="background-image:url('https://icons.duckduckgo.com/ip3/youtube.com.ico')"></span><span class="title">YouTube</span><span class="dom">youtube.com</span></div>
            <div class="trow"><span class="fav" style="background-image:url('https://icons.duckduckgo.com/ip3/netflix.com.ico')"></span><span class="title">Netflix</span><span class="dom">netflix.com</span></div>
          </div>
          <div class="foot">esc to dismiss · /group moves this tab · ⌘1–9 jumps groups</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <figcaption>A group name stays with the active task, while the rest of the session can remain folded away.</figcaption>
  </figure>
  <section class="feature-copy-grid feature-copy-grid--top" aria-labelledby="group-behavior-title">
    <div><p class="section-kicker">keep work in context</p><h2 id="group-behavior-title">Groups have names, not colors.</h2></div>
    <div class="feature-copy-list">
      <article><h3>Name the task, then keep moving.</h3><p>Use <code>/group work</code> to create or join a named group from the active tab. A group exists only while it has tabs in it.</p></article>
      <article><h3>Keep the active group close.</h3><p>The Island shows the active group's tabs and name. Other groups live in the expanded panel until you choose to switch back to them.</p></article>
      <article><h3>Fold the rest without losing the thread.</h3><p>Groups can tuck away in the panel, and the Quick Switcher finds them by name when it is time to return.</p></article>
    </div>
  </section>
  <aside class="truth-note" aria-labelledby="groups-note-title"><p class="section-kicker">fewer things asking for attention</p><h2 id="groups-note-title">A group is a focus tool, not another layer of browser chrome.</h2><p>Blanc gives the active task a quiet place in the Island while keeping the rest of your session nearby. Pinned tabs stay with their group, and a plain new tab starts ungrouped.</p><a class="text-link" href="/features/command-palette" data-track="feature_cta_click" data-feature="tab-groups" data-cta-position="related-feature">Use commands to move through groups <span aria-hidden="true">↗</span></a></aside>
  <section class="feature-close" aria-labelledby="groups-close-title"><p class="section-kicker">make room for the task</p><h2 id="groups-close-title">Keep the session. Lose the tab-strip noise.</h2><a class="cta" href="/download" data-track="feature_cta_click" data-feature="tab-groups" data-cta-position="feature-close">download blanc</a></section>
</main>
</BaseLayout>
